Overview

Concordance analysis allows us to group strains that are genetically almost identical into an isotype. The following table summarizes the number of isotypes from previous and current releases, and the number of strains that belong to those isotypes.

Isotypes Strains Included Strains with WGS data Strains with RAD-seq data
Isotypes from Previous Release 327 779 639 140
New Isotypes from Current Release 76 134 134 0
Total 403 913 773 140


Concordance score distribution and cutoff

We examined the pairwise concordance scores of all strains. Concordance values for every pair of strains were calculated as the number of shared variant sites divided by the total number of variants called for each pair. If the concordance score was more than 0.9995, the strain pair is grouped into the same isotype.

Changes from previous release


  • Strain JU1511 was re-assigned to isotype JU792 from isotype JU1581. In the previous release (20180527), the JU1511 isotype grouping was based solely on RAD-seq data. We recently performed whole-genome sequencing of this strain and changed its isotype based on these new data.




  • Strain JU1580 was merged into the JU1793 isotype because it grouped with every strain of this isotype.
